snippet: Aleksandar Vucic, expected to be Serbia’s next prime minister, recast himself as a pro-Western liberal in a transformation viewed as remarkable.
abstract: Serbia's election commission says that governing center-right Serbian Progressive Party has won 48 percent of the vote and its leader Aleksandar Vucic is expected to become prime minister.
lead_paragraph: Aleksandar Vucic, expected to be Serbia’s next prime minister, recast himself as a pro-Western liberal in a transformation viewed as remarkable.

headline.main: Ultranationalist-Turned-Liberal Is Expected to Lead Serbia
headline.print_headline: Serbia: Pro-Western Liberal Expected to Become the Next Prime Minister
